      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a driver-focused example featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, equipped with individual throttle bodies and double VANOS for exceptional throttle response. Power is managed through a tactile 6-speed manual gearbox and an M-Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis has been properly sorted with documented subframe reinforcement and a recent cooling system refresh. Suspension remains tight with upgraded poly-bushings, while the braking system utilizes cross-drilled rotors for consistent thermal management. Finished in Carbon Black, the exterior and Nappa leather interior show minor wear consistent with a well-maintained enthusiast vehicle. This M3 has undergone a recent valve adjustment and is mechanically prepared for the 8,000 RPM redline.",
